        <h2>What is Neo4j?</h2>

        <p>Neo4j is a <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/neotechnology.com/');"
                         href="http://neotechnology.com/">commercially supported</a>
            open-source graph database, that is:</p>

        <div class="span5">

            <p>A graph database stores data in nodes and relationships with properties on both, something we call a <a
                    href="/learn/propertygraph">Property Graph</a>.
                Nodes are simply data records. Relationships are the connections between records.</p>

            <p>Neo4j is both an open source project, and a commercial product. in a GPLv3 Community edition, with
                Advanced and Enterprise editions available under both the AGPLv3 and commercial licenses, supported by
                Neo Technology.</p>

            <ul>
                <li>intuitive, using a graph model for data representation</li>
                <li>reliable, with fully ACID transactions</li>
                <li>durable, using disk-based, native storage</li>
                <li>massively scalable, up to several billion nodes/relationships/properties</li>
                <li>highly-available, when sharded to scale out across multiple machines</li>
                <li>expressive, with a powerful traversal framework for high-speed graph queries</li>
                <li>embeddable, with a few small jars</li>
                <li>simple, accessible by a convenient <a
                        onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/docs.neo4j.org/chunked/stable/rest-api.html');"
                        href="http://docs.neo4j.org/chunked/<%= neo4jGA.version %>/rest-api.html">REST interface</a> or
                    object-oriented <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/api.neo4j.org/');"
                                       href="http://api.neo4j.org/<%= neo4jGA.version %>">API</a></li>
            </ul>
